{"lemma":"زَوالٌ","slug":"زَوالٌ","root":"ز.#.ل","root_slug":"ز-_-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-_-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"زَوال","root":"زول","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18429","n18431"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of زَالَ (zāla) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"end, passage, extinction, disappearance, vanishing, cessation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"noon"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/za.waːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18429","headword_ar":"زَوَالٌ","root":"zwl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawiylN","text_ar":"زَوِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawolN","text_ar":"زَوْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) are inf. ns. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAla","text_ar":"زَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  And all signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Motion, commotion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agitation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in explanation of the first and last, and K in explanation of the second.) [Hence,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAla","text_ar":"زَالَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawaAluhu","text_ar":"زَوَالُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawaAlahu","text_ar":"زَوَالَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAla","text_ar":"زَالَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (accord. to different copies of the K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu zawaAlahu","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ زَوَالَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAla","text_ar":"زَالَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zyl","text_ar":"زيل"},{"kind":"text","text":", and TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu zawaAlahu","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ زَوَالَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azaAla","text_ar":"اَزَالَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zyl","text_ar":"زيل"},{"kind":"text","text":", and K and TA,) are imprecations of destruction, or perdition, or death, (S, K,) and trial, or affliction, upon him to whom they relate: (S:) or such are the [second and] third and fourth of these phrases: but the first is a prayer for one's continuance where he is, [or his continuance in life; lit.] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May his motion cease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may he continue where he is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continue in life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and, as expl. by ISk, the [second and] third and fourth [lit.] signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God cause his motion to cease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God, put an end to his life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] these phrases being similar to the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asokata A@ll~`hu naAm~atahu","text_ar":"اَسْكَتَ ا@للّٰهُ نَامَّتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Thus all four have virtually the same lit. signification. And the first has also another meaning; as will be seen below.] El-Aashà says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"h`*aA Aln~ahaAru badaA lahaA mino ham~ihaA\n                      \n                     \n                        zawaAlahaA ↓ \n      maA baAluhaA biAll~ayoli zaAla"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) [app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is the day-time: an opinion has arisen in her mind such as to turn her from her former opinion"},{"kind":"text","text":"and induce her to absent herself, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaA='N","text_ar":"بَدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", I suppose, being understood after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaA lahaA","text_ar":"بَدَا لَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as it is after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaA lahumo","text_ar":"بَدَا لَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur xii. 35,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence of her anxiety: what will be her case in the night? may it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(her phantom)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be absent, like as she is absent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] the meaning is said to be,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAla AlxayaAlu zawaAlahaA","text_ar":"زَالَ الخَيَالُ زَوَالَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": IAar says, he disliked the phantom only because it roused his desire: or ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAla","text_ar":"زَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be here syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azaAla","text_ar":"اَزَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", so that] the meaning may be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu zawaAlahaA","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ زَوَالَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azaAla","text_ar":"اَزَالَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God make her motion to cease"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and this is corroborated by the reading of AA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawaAluhaA","text_ar":"زَوَالُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the nom. case, [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawaAluhaA","text_ar":"زَوَالُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAla","text_ar":"زَالَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may her motion cease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] which makes this an instance of [the license termed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_iqowaA='","text_ar":"الاـِقْوَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": this, he says, is an old proverbial phrase of the Arabs, and El-Aashà has used it as he heard it: others than AA read ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawaAlahaA","text_ar":"زَوَالَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",] in the accus. case, without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iqowaA='","text_ar":"اـِقْوَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", holding the meaning to be, may her phantom be absent from us in the night like as she herself is absent in the day-time. (TA.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawiyluhu","text_ar":"زَوِيلُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziyla","text_ar":"زِيلَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", likewise, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His motion ceased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may his motion cease:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Z,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became fixed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"motionless, from fear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may he become so."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zyl","text_ar":"زيل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also another rendering of this phrase in the next paragraph.] One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlEawiylu","text_ar":"وَالعَوِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu Alz~awiylu","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ الزَّوِيلُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Commotion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agitation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disquietude of mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and wailing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raising of the voice in weeping, overcame him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)       -A2-  See also the next paragraph, in three places."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n18431","headword_ar":"زَوَّالٌ","root":"zwl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having much"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawol","text_ar":"زَوْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"motion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Accord. to J, it occurs in an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urojuwzap","text_ar":"اُرْجُوزَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", cited by AA, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That moves much in his gait, but traverses a short space:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the right word in this case is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaw~aAk","text_ar":"زَوَّاك"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is shown by the rhyme. (IB, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}